cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

This paper discusses the deployment of deep neural networks (DNNs) in hybrid computing environments, which involves cloud, edge, and end devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also proposes a self-adaptive discrete particle swarm optimization (PSO) algorithm using genetic algorithm (GA) operators, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with optimizing the system cost while accomplishing the offloaded layers with their deadline constraints, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the characteristics of DNNs partitioning and layers offloading over the cloud, which is related to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Finally, the paper compares the proposed offloading strategy with benchmark solutions, which is related to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
